ABUJA – Borno State governor, Babagana Umaru Zullum who is also the Chairman of the APC Policy Conference Committee has stressed a need for the ruling party to do an introspection of it achievement with a view to draw a template for future policy direction for the party. Represented by the Secretary of the committee and Director General of the National Orientation Agency (NOA), Dr Garba Abari the governor said the policy conference scheduled for YarAdua Centre, Friday in Abuja will see leaders of the party engage sector experts on “current and future policy direction ofthe party and provide a reform agenda which the party will drive over the next phase of our administration building on the current achievements, including the outcomes for State and Local governments”. Among other things, he said the conference would seek to address various segments around governance, economy and social environment with the aim to re-enkindle investors’ confidence in the Nigerian economy. The NOA boss who briefed journalists in company with Representatives of Governors Zullum and Kayode Fayemi, co-Chairman of the APC Policy Conference Committee said the objectives of the committee would include a review of the performance of APC-controlled national and subnational governments, an Analysis and introspective pathways towards mapping the future to bridge the gaps and unlock the productive potential of the country. *Discuss the approaches required towards achieving an inclusive and coherent policy trajectory for the party in government.*Harmonise a sustainable implementation agenda with the implementation framework as a follow-up to existing plans, policies, programmes and projects. According to Dr Abari, the APC Policy Conference will be structured into different panel discussions that will focus on core thematic areas as follows: economy, governance, and human development. “This will enable resource persons and participants to create a central spine that holds the party’s development agenda since 2015.The sessions will be designed to be intense, interactive, and stimulating between the panellists and participants. Among dignitaries that participate in the Policy Conference include President Mohammadu Buhari, Prof Yemi Osinbajo, President of Senate Ahmed Lawan, and his colleagues, Speaker of the House of Representatives Femi Gbajabiamila